catalogOutcomes:
Students will gain the knowledge about sex, gender, and sexuality development and changes over the lifespan and the tools to: 
1) apply multi-disciplinary perspectives to developmental theories of sexual change over the lifespan;
2) think critically about issues of sex, gender, and sexuality during class discussions;
3) develop writing skills for both an academic and layperson audience;
4) analyze critically the accuracy and scope of sexual science conveyed in both peer-reviewed journal articles and popular media through assignments, and 5) discuss and think through research ethics in the context of studying sex, gender, and sexuality during different developmental milestones and understanding the ethical treatment of gender and sexual minorities.
